main event: A brightly white oval-shaped object was observed in the sky over Lancaster, Texas, which burst into a horizontal luminous disc and then resumed its original saucer-like shape.
interesting points: The object moved at an altitude of 10 to 15 inches and at an estimated visual speed of 260 mph.
The object disappeared at an elevation angle of 20 to 30 degrees azimuth.
The report includes a Project 10073 Record Card, which was used to document UFO sightings as part of Project Blue Book.

The report's conclusions are inconclusive, with options such as 'Possibly Balloon', 'Probably Aircraft', and 'Probably astronomical' checked, as well as 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation' and 'Unknown'.
